cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about Named Entity Recognition (NER) using neural networks and focuses on the use of lexical features. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves training a low-dimensional vector space, which suggests the possibility of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) being relevant categories. Additionally, the paper involves distant supervision and the use of Wikipedia, which could fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
